description:
&lt;p&gt;Nuffield Health Warwickshire Hospital is currently seeking to recruit a highly motivated, friendly and professional Diagnostic Radiographer, with a post graduate certificate in Mammography, to join the team in our busy department on a part-time, fixed term basis to cover maternity leave.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the ability to work within the team whilst also being able to use your own initiative and work independently during the day and when on-call. The hours are predominantly between 8.30am and 6pm, five days a week, with weekday and weekend on-call (on a rotational basis).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The day-to-day duties will involve monitoring of clinic lists and Mammography of our out-patients on both a booked and ad-hoc basis when clinics are running in OPD. You will have the chance to not only complete Mammography examinations but assist with US of breast work where needed, with expert guidance from both our Radiologists and Radiology Assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You should be able to demonstrate a proven clinical experience in a wide range of radiographic techniques, a high level of accuracy and attention to detail, good computer literacy with flexibility and adaptability to meet the changing needs of the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you wish to discuss this vacancy informally, please feel free to contact the Department Manager, Shawn Anderson on 01926 562562.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential requirements include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DCR or BSc in Diagnostic Radiography, current HCPC registration and evidence of CPD and a Mammography PgC.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key employee benefits can include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A competitive salary, the offer of additional hours, overtime, enhancements and on-call payments, continuing professional and career development, generous holiday and leave arrangements, flexible pension options, life assurance and healthcare schemes, health assessments (after a qualifying period), free membership of our fantastic Nuffield Health Fitness &amp; Wellbeing Centres, with heavily subsidised memberships for family, cycle to work scheme, childcare vouchers, employee assistance programme for professional advice and counselling – legal, financial, etc. and employee discounts on a wide range of products and/or services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Nuffield Health Warwickshire Hospital has been rated as a ‘Good’ hospital by the CQC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be your best and join us in building a healthier nation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary - Up to £32,565 per annum&lt;br /&gt;Closing date - 10/11/2020&lt;br /&gt;Location - Warwickshire Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type - FIxed Term - 12 month - Maternity Cover&lt;br /&gt;Weekly Hours - 37.5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Nuffield Health is committed to equal opportunities in the recruitment, training, and development of our employees. We have a duty to apply to the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) for disclosure on successful candidates.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
